# Creating normal distribution with given length.
    normal_distribution = norm.rvs(size=length)
    # Creating probability density function for normal distribution.
    x = np.linspace(normal_distribution.min(), normal_distribution.max(), 100)
    y = norm.pdf(x, normal_distribution.mean(), normal_distribution.std())
    # Plotting histogram for normal distribution.
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(normal_distribution, bins=20, density=True, alpha=0.5, label='histogram')
    ax.plot(x, y, label='normal distribution')
    ax.set_title('Probability density function (normal distribution)')
    ax.legend()

    return normal_distribution, ax
